{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Le sculture da Alesa","Portale","2009","\u003Cspan>Elisa Chiara Portale, «Le sculture da Alesa», in \u003Ci>Alaisa-Halaesa. Scavi e ricerche (1970-2007)\u003C/i>, a c. di G. Scibona e G. Tigano (Messina: Sicania, 2009), 67–92\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/BCIMMIKZ",[8,129],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":27,"handNote":34,"date":48,"places":53,"geo":63,"provenance":55,"provenanceGeo":67,"country":70,"region":71,"settlement":55,"repository":72,"idno":76,"textLang":79,"tmNumber":83,"facsimile":84,"letterHeights":91,"publications":92,"zotero":102,"keywords":112,"html":122,"bibl":123},"ISic000768","Dedication by a sevir to Concordia",{"_":12},"edited",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"dedication","#function.dedication","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},"marble (white)","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html","",{"layout":28},{"p":29,"rs":30,"damage":26},"The epigraphic face is preserved for a width of 12.5 cm, with two lines of Latin letters filling the available field.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":35,"dimensions":36},"The letters are tall, neatly cut and closely spaced (height c.30mm), and words are separated by simple triangular interpuncts. The letters are lightly serifed. E is tall and narrow, T has a curved cross-bar, rising to the right.",[37,44],{"type":38,"l":39,"from":40,"to":41,"h":42,"unit":43},"letterHeight","Line 1-2","line1","line2","30","mm",{"type":45,"l":46,"from":40,"to":41,"h":47,"unit":43},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","?",{"_":49,"notBefore":50,"notAfter":51,"precision":52},"Late 1st century CE, or 2nd century CE",51,200,"low",[54,58],{"_":55,"type":56,"ref":57},"Halaesa","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462225",{"_":59,"type":60,"ref":61,"offset":62},"Castel di Tusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525099","near",[64],[65,66],37.99907,14.26197,[68,69],37.998047,14.262635,"Italy","Sicily",{"_":73,"role":74,"ref":75},"Antiquarium e sito archeologico di Halaesa ","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/053",{"_":77,"type":78},"ME 20226","inventory",{"_":80,"mainLang":81,"languages":82},"Latin","la",[80],"175722",{"n":85,"url":86,"height":87,"width":88,"desc":89,"surfaceType":90},"screen","ISic000768_tiled.tif","3395px","7360px","Photo J. Prag, courtesy Soprintendenza di Messina","front",[],[93,94,95,96,97,98,99,100,101],"L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Scibona, 1971, Epigraphica Halaesina I","Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano","Manganaro, 1989, Iscrizioni Latine nuove e vecchie della Sicilia","Facella, 2006, Alesa Arconidea: ricerche su un'antica città della Sicilia tirrenica","Scibona, 2008, The Epigraphs","Portale, 2009, Le sculture da Alesa","Prestianni Giallombardo, 2012, Spazio pubblico e memoria civica. Le epigrafi dall'agora di Alesa","Prag, Tigano, 2017, Alesa Archonidea: il lapidarium",[103,104,105,106,107,108,109,110,111],"R46KDTZX","UISW82JC","RZSFKACR","EZMBJ6GN","J4XWZPV6","6GFVUASD","BCIMMIKZ","CJISRIUV","MI64NB9L",[113,114,115,15,19,23,116,117,118,119,116,120,121,81],"isic000768","dedication by a sevir to concordia",{"_":12},"halaesa","castel di tusa","italy","sicily","antiquarium e sito archeologico di halaesa","latin","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>Conco]ṛdiae · Aug[ustae\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ethus · sev[ir\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":124,"ptr":125,"ref":127,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},"85-87",{"target":126},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/BCIMMIKZ",{"_":128,"target":128},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001670",{"file":130,"uri":130,"title":131,"status":132,"editionAuthor":13,"type":133,"objectType":134,"material":137,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":138,"handNote":142,"date":154,"places":159,"geo":162,"provenance":55,"provenanceGeo":164,"country":70,"region":71,"settlement":55,"repository":167,"idno":168,"textLang":170,"tmNumber":172,"facsimile":173,"letterHeights":178,"publications":179,"zotero":181,"keywords":183,"html":187,"bibl":188},"ISic000804","Dedication of a statue to Ceres, by Iulius Acilius Hermes, sevir",{"_":12},{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},{"_":135,"ana":136,"ref":21},"statue base","#object.statue_base",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},{"layout":139},{"p":140,"rs":141,"damage":26},"The Latin text is engraved over two lines (letters c.20 mm high, but of uneven height), to a maximum length of 52 cm.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"lettering":143,"dimensions":144}," The letters show some irregularity, with fairly pronounced serifs, and lengthy tails to the letter R. The first two words are separated from the rest by a space; an interpunct is visible at the end of the dedicant’s name, and the final abbreviated phrase is separated from the rest by a large hedera (ivy leaf). The letter I in line 1 is frequently taller than the rest (but so too is the first L in line 1); the final I of line 1 is somewhat irregularly carved.",[145,148,151],{"type":38,"l":146,"from":40,"to":40,"h":147,"unit":43},"Line 1","18-25",{"type":38,"l":149,"from":41,"to":41,"h":150,"unit":43},"Line 2","19-23",{"type":45,"l":152,"from":40,"to":41,"h":153,"unit":43},"Interlineation lines 1-2","7-15",{"_":155,"notBefore":156,"notAfter":157,"evidence":158},"Statue can be dated stylistically to the late Antonine period (i.e. the 180s or 190s CE), and the text is compatible with such a date.",180,199,"context",[160,161],{"_":55,"type":56,"ref":57},{"_":59,"type":60,"ref":61,"offset":62},[163],[65,66],[165,166],37.998037,14.262643,{"_":73,"role":74,"ref":75},{"_":169,"type":78},"ME 20194",{"_":80,"mainLang":81,"languages":171},[80],"175724",{"n":85,"url":174,"height":175,"width":176,"desc":177,"surfaceType":90},"ISic000804_tiled.tif","1949px","4512px","Photo J. Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina",[],[93,94,95,180,99,100,101],"Scibona, 2008, Statuary",[103,104,105,182,109,110,111],"EQC3W4UU",[184,185,186,15,135,23,116,117,118,119,116,120,121,81],"isic000804","dedication of a statue to ceres, by iulius acilius hermes, sevir",{"_":12},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Cereri sacr(um) \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> Iulius Acilius Her-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>mes · pro honor(e) seviratus ❦ d(eae) d(onum) d(edit) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":189,"ptr":190,"ref":191,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},"80-87 fig.7",{"target":126},{"_":128,"target":128}],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
